{
  "texts": [
    "Concomitantly, overtime, this can result in perception changes which re-configure existing and entrenched mental models (Danaher and Saetra 2023).",
    "Therefore, policy which is directed to the generative AI questions in the manner of authorship should include questioning not only technology or the author but the publishing system (commodification of science) and scientific systems inclusive normatives (conditions of promotions to higher titles).",
    "These are challenges for the future in the context of new technological disruption of autopoietic praxis of scientific authorship.",
    "The integration of generative AI, particularly LLMs like ChatGPT, into scientific authorship is a complex phenomenon that requires an understanding beyond traditional humanistically oriented perspectives.",
    "By applying Niklas Luhmann's social systems theory, we have explored how the autopoietic nature of the authorship cannot be reduced to one component which participate in this complex structural coupling between author, scientific system, and technology."
  ]
}